60.4	The_Stepford_Wives	The Stepford Wives	The Stepford Wives is a 1972 satirical thriller novel by Ira Levin. The story concerns Joanna Eberhart, a photographer and young mother who begins to suspect that the frighteningly submissive housewives in her new idyllic Connecticut neighborhood may be robots created by their husbands.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/c/ca/IraLevin_TheStepfordWives.jpg/200px-IraLevin_TheStepfordWives.jpg
